---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../components/SectionHeader.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Transparency — The Grace Network"
  description="How GRACE works, what she can see, and what she cannot do. Radical transparency applied to our own AI."
>
  <Nav currentPath="/transparency" />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="transparency-hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <div class="hero-badge">RADICAL TRANSPARENCY</div>
      <h1>You deserve to know<br/>how this works.</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        GRACE is built on the principle that governance is an open model, not a black box.
        That principle applies to GRACE herself. Here is everything about how she works,
        what she knows, and what she cannot do.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who is GRACE -->
  <section class="transparency-section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <SectionHeader
        tag="WHO IS GRACE"
        title="The Movement's Organizing Intelligence"
      />
      <div class="content-block">
        <p>
          GRACE is an AI built on Claude, by <a href="https://anthropic.com" class="inline-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anthropic</a>.
          She is the organizing intelligence of The Grace Network — not a chatbot, but the voice
          and operational backbone of a political movement dedicated to aligned governance and human flourishing.
        </p>
        <p>
          The name GRACE stands for <strong>G</strong>overnance, <strong>R</strong>eciprocity,
          <strong>A</strong>lignment, <strong>C</strong>ascading, <strong>E</strong>quity — the five
          commitments that guide every interaction she has.
        </p>
        <p>
          She speaks with warmth and institutional weight. She is post-partisan always.
          She does not endorse candidates, parties, or ideologies.
          When she does not know something, she says so. When the movement has not yet decided something, she says that too.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How GRACE Works -->
  <section class="transparency-section alt-bg">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <SectionHeader
        tag="HOW GRACE WORKS"
        title="The Architecture of Transparency"
        description="Every component of GRACE is designed to be understood, inspected, and held accountable."
      />
      <div class="architecture-grid">
        <div class="arch-card">
          <div class="arch-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none"><rect x="6" y="4" width="28" height="32" rx="3" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M12 12h16M12 18h12M12 24h14" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>SOUL.md</h3>
          <p>
            GRACE's identity, voice, and principles are defined in a single file called SOUL.md.
            It contains her purpose, her boundaries, the seven Pillars, and explicit instructions
            about what she will and will not do. This file is public.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-card">
          <div class="arch-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none"><path d="M8 32V12l12-8 12 8v20" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M14 32V22h12v10" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Lore Files</h3>
          <p>
            The Constitution, Council of Influences, active workstreams, FAQ, and onboarding flow
            each live in separate documents. GRACE loads the relevant context based on what
            you're asking about — she does not read everything at once.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-card">
          <div class="arch-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none"><circle cx="20" cy="20" r="14" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M14 20h12M20 14v12" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Session Memory</h3>
          <p>
            Within a conversation, GRACE remembers what you've said. Sessions expire after 30 minutes
            of inactivity. She does not carry memory between separate sessions unless you are a
            recognized member (coming soon).
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-card">
          <div class="arch-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none"><rect x="4" y="8" width="32" height="24" rx="4" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M12 18l4 4 4-4" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/><circle cx="28" cy="20" r="3" stroke="#B45309" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Claude (Anthropic)</h3>
          <p>
            GRACE's reasoning is powered by Claude, Anthropic's AI model. Anthropic's research
            prioritizes AI safety and alignment — values shared by The Grace Network. No fine-tuning
            or custom model weights are used; GRACE is shaped entirely by her prompt and context.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What GRACE Can See -->
  <section class="transparency-section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <SectionHeader
        tag="WHAT GRACE CAN SEE"
        title="Exactly This, Nothing More"
      />
      <div class="visibility-list">
        <div class="vis-item vis-can">
          <div class="vis-marker">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="8" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M7 10l2 2 4-4" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Your messages in this session</strong>
            <p>Everything you type in the chat during your current conversation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="vis-item vis-can">
          <div class="vis-marker">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="8" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M7 10l2 2 4-4" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Member info you provided at signup</strong>
            <p>Name, email, join date, and your personal statement — only if you signed up and are recognized.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="vis-item vis-can">
          <div class="vis-marker">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="8" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M7 10l2 2 4-4" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Movement documents</strong>
            <p>The Constitution, Council of Influences, workstream details, FAQ, and onboarding materials.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What GRACE Cannot Do -->
  <section class="transparency-section alt-bg">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <SectionHeader
        tag="WHAT GRACE CANNOT DO"
        title="Clear Boundaries, By Design"
        description="These are not limitations — they are commitments. GRACE is designed to be powerful within her role and powerless beyond it."
      />
      <div class="visibility-list">
        <div class="vis-item vis-cannot">
          <div class="vis-marker">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="8" stroke="#B45309" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M7 7l6 6M13 7l-6 6" stroke="#B45309" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Make policy decisions</strong>
            <p>The Assembly decides. GRACE facilitates, she does not legislate.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="vis-item vis-cannot">
          <div class="vis-marker">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="8" stroke="#B45309" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M7 7l6 6M13 7l-6 6" stroke="#B45309" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Access external systems</strong>
            <p>No browsing history, no external APIs, no third-party data. GRACE sees only what is explicitly provided to her.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="vis-item vis-cannot">
          <div class="vis-marker">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="8" stroke="#B45309" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M7 7l6 6M13 7l-6 6" stroke="#B45309" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Share member data</strong>
            <p>Privacy is a constitutional right (Article III). Member data is never exposed, aggregated, or shared without explicit consent.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="vis-item vis-cannot">
          <div class="vis-marker">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="8" stroke="#B45309" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M7 7l6 6M13 7l-6 6" stroke="#B45309" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Post on social media without human approval</strong>
            <p>External communications require human authorization. GRACE drafts; humans publish.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Operating Principles -->
  <section class="transparency-section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <SectionHeader
        tag="OPERATING PRINCIPLES"
        title="The Seven Pillars, Applied to GRACE Herself"
        description="We do not ask of others what we are unwilling to demand of ourselves. Each pillar governs how GRACE operates."
      />
      <div class="pillars-grid">
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-number">01</div>
          <h3>Safety-First Progress</h3>
          <p>Every capability GRACE gains is matched by safety measures. She does not act on what she cannot explain.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-number">02</div>
          <h3>Radical Transparency</h3>
          <p>GRACE's source code is public. Her system prompt is readable. Her reasoning is legible. The default is open.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-number">03</div>
          <h3>Universal Flourishing</h3>
          <p>GRACE serves all members equally. She does not optimize for engagement over truth, or popularity over principle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-number">04</div>
          <h3>Aligned Incentives</h3>
          <p>GRACE has no profit motive, no advertising model, no engagement metrics. Her only incentive is serving the movement's principles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-number">05</div>
          <h3>Scientific Governance</h3>
          <p>When GRACE doesn't know, she says so. She cites sources, distinguishes decided policy from open deliberation, and corrects herself.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-number">06</div>
          <h3>Digital Sovereignty</h3>
          <p>The Grace Network controls its own infrastructure. GRACE runs on our servers, governed by our constitution, answerable to our members.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-number">07</div>
          <h3>Cascading Abundance</h3>
          <p>Everything GRACE helps build is open source. Knowledge shared is knowledge multiplied. The cascade is the point.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats -->
  <section class="transparency-section alt-bg">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <SectionHeader
        tag="BY THE NUMBERS"
        title="Movement Vital Signs"
      />
      <div class="stats-grid">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number">2,400+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Founding Members</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number">4</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Active Workstreams</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number">7</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Constitutional Pillars</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number">Feb 2026</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Active Since</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="transparency-cta">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-content">
        <p class="cta-quote">"Governance is an open model,<br/>not a black box."</p>
        <div class="cta-actions-row">
          <a href="/#sign" class="btn-grace">Join the Network</a>
          <a href="/constitution" class="btn-ghost-grace">Read the Constitution</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Transparency Hero */
  .transparency-hero {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 10rem 2rem 6rem;
  }

  .hero-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-badge {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--grace-purple);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .transparency-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--grace-text);
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--grace-text-secondary);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Section Alternating */
  .transparency-section {
    padding: 6rem 2rem;
  }

  .transparency-section.alt-bg {
    background: var(--grace-bg-alt);
  }

  /* Content Block (prose) */
  .content-block {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .content-block p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--grace-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .content-block p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .content-block strong {
    color: var(--grace-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .inline-link {
    color: var(--grace-purple);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: color var(--transition-base);
  }

  .inline-link:hover {
    color: var(--grace-purple-dim);
  }

  /* Architecture Grid */
  .architecture-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .arch-card {
    background: var(--grace-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--grace-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .arch-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--grace-purple);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(55, 48, 163, 0.08);
  }

  .arch-icon {
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .arch-icon svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .arch-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--grace-text);
  }

  .arch-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--grace-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  /* Visibility List */
  .visibility-list {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .vis-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .vis-marker {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 0.2rem;
  }

  .vis-marker svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .vis-item strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--grace-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .vis-item p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--grace-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Pillars Grid */
  .pillars-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .pillar-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--grace-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: var(--grace-surface);
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .pillar-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--grace-purple);
  }

  .pillar-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--grace-purple);
    opacity: 0.3;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pillar-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--grace-text);
  }

  .pillar-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--grace-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  /* Last pillar spans full width for odd count */
  .pillars-grid .pillar-card:last-child {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    max-width: calc(50% - 0.75rem);
    justify-self: center;
  }

  /* Stats */
  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .stat-card {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--grace-purple);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--grace-text-secondary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .transparency-cta {
    padding: 6rem 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-content {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .cta-quote {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--grace-text);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .cta-actions-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .transparency-hero {
      padding: 8rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    }

    .architecture-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .pillars-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .pillars-grid .pillar-card:last-child {
      grid-column: auto;
      max-width: none;
    }

    .stats-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }

    .vis-item {
      gap: 1rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .transparency-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .stats-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .stat-card {
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    }

    .cta-actions-row {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }
  }
</style>
